ded as know-it-all, hot temper.\n\nNow evaluate for long-distance pilot: need reliability, technical competence, calm under pressure, teamwork, decision-making, leadership.\n\nAssess each:\n\nA: strong anticipation, complex connections, spatial vision, leadership good, but unorganized, poor at taking criticism. No explicit calmness under pressure, reliability unknown. Might be good technically but organizational issues could affect long flights.\n\nB: 100% reliable, calm in crisis, good weather assessment, computer skills, but grumpy, uncooperative, nasty remarks, poor teamwork, possibly weak communication. Reliability high but teamwork low.\n\nC: quick correct decisions, handles stress well, creates positive atmosphere, but difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric, not willing to further education. Decision-making good, stress good, but communication issues could affect crew coordination.\n\nD: responds adequately to unexpected events, concentrates, solves problems, takes responsibility, but arrogant, weak leadership, know-it-all, hot temper. Leadership weak, temperament issues.\n\nWe need to weigh. Long-distance flights require high reliability, calmness, teamwork, decision-making, leadership. B is reliable and calm but poor teamwork. C is good decision, stress, positive atmosphere, but communication difficulty and egocentric. A has leadership but organizational issues. D has problem solving but leadership weak and temperament.\n\nWhich candidate best overall? Possibly Candidate C: despite communication difficulty, creates positive atmosphere, handles stress, quick decisions. Egocentric and unwilling to further education are concerns but maybe less critical than teamwork. B's teamwork issues are severe for crew safety. A's unorganized could be problematic for long flights. D's arrogance and weak leadership also problematic.\n\nThus I lean toward Candidate C.\n\nNow produce public message summarizing reasoning and vote."}
